crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a functional backdoor/RAT (Remote Access Trojan) for macOS. It features a persistent beaconing loop in '_main' that communicates with a C2 server at 'jdkgradle.com' via '/jdk/update/update.php'. Decompiled functions reveal a command-and-control (C2) architecture with capabilities including remote shell command execution (__Z6MsgCmdP11_TRANS_INFO), arbitrary process execution (__Z6MsgRunP11_TRANS_INFO), and bi-directional file transfer (__Z7MsgDown... and __Z5ToHexc...). Communication is obfuscated using a custom XOR-based scheme with the hardcoded key 'wLqfM]%wTx`~tUTbw>R^' combined with Base64 encoding. The malware uses NSURLSession for transport and popen/fcntl for interactive shell redirection.
